GETSTR - Asks you to input a string (arguments are: maxlen,default,row,col)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Argument(s): from 0 to 4, Integer String Integer Integer 
   Result type: String 
   Aliases    : GETSTRING
   Category   : User and file interaction functions

   Example: 
     C:> ASET -p X := GETSTR(3,'AB',1,1)
     X=ABC


